comments: I noticed that pink and yellow tended to end in -cow, but it was not true for all shapes. The light blue pentagon and the light blue star had completely unique endings, so they were easier to remember. I did not pen and paper or right down any notes, My only strategy was to try to figure out patterns and rely on my memory, but I don't think I succeeded. I found the last aspect of the study pretty difficult because working with another person when I did not have the language down made me unsure if I was remembering what I just learned.
